The paper focuses on the development of an integrated software and hardware system for autonomous mobile robot navigation in uneven and unstructured indoor environments. This involves the use of perception and navigation capabilities, as well as the creation of a 3D OctoMap representation and multilayer 2D occupancy maps. These topics are all closely related to the field of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the use of RGB-D data and 2D laser data for mapping and navigation suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of a variable step size Rapidly Exploring Random Trees algorithm, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the integration of software and hardware components for autonomous navigation suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
